  "reason_thou": "1. Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash is an assertion failure in
SystemZTTIImpl::getCastInstrCost asserting !Dst->isVectorTy() when Src is scalar and Dst
is vector. This indicates that the SLP vectorizer invoked TTI::getCastInstrCost with
mismatched scalar/vector types for Src/Dst.\n\n2. Analyzing opt's Log:\n- SLP is
vectorizing a bundle of zext <4 x i1> -> <4 x i32> and compares. The debug log shows it
\u201cadded a vector of casts.\u201d\n- The stack points to BoUpSLP::getTreeCost at line
11797 as the site of the problematic TTI call. This is inside the \u201cAdd reduced value
cost, if resized.\u201d block which computes MinBitWidths and adds a cast cost.\n- In this
block, DstTy is set to Root.Scalars.front()->getType(). For the current tree, Root is a
vector zext, so DstTy is a vector type. However, the code constructs SrcTy as a scalar
IntegerType and calls TTI->getCastInstrCost with Dst=vector, Src=scalar, which SystemZ TTI
does not expect for RecipThroughput cost kind.\n\n3. Root Cause Analysis:\nThe SLP
vectorizer's getTreeCost incorrectly treats DstTy as a scalar when building the SrcTy for
the cast cost adjustment. Specifically, it:\n- Calculates OriginalSz as
DL->getTypeSizeInBits(DstTy), which for vectors is the total bit size, not the element
size.\n- Builds SrcTy as a scalar IntegerType even when DstTy is a vector, leading to a
vector/scalar mismatch in the TTI cost query.\n- This causes SystemZ TTI to assert because
the non-vector path is entered with a vector Dst type.\n\n4. Proposed Edit Point(s)\nFile:
llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp\nLocation: BoUpSLP::getTreeCost, lines
11788-11800.\nEdits:\n- Compute OriginalSz from the scalar element type rather than the
whole type.\n- When DstTy is a vector, construct a matching vector SrcTy using the same VF
and the reduced scalar type; otherwise keep SrcTy scalar.\n- Keep the opcode selection
logic, but apply based on element size.\n\nConcrete change:\nReplace the block that
computes OriginalSz, SrcTy, and calls getCastInstrCost with the following logic (in-place
at lines 11788-11800):\n\n  Type *DstTy = Root.Scalars.front()->getType();\n  unsigned
OriginalSz = DL->getTypeSizeInBits(DstTy->getScalarType());\n  unsigned SrcSz =
ReductionBitWidth == 0 ? BWIt->second.first : ReductionBitWidth;\n  if (OriginalSz !=
SrcSz) {\n    unsigned Opcode = Instruction::Trunc;\n    if (OriginalSz > SrcSz)\n
